The paper deals with distributed algorithms for solving linear algebraic equations, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). The use of network flows and consensus dynamics also suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and network science (cs.NE). Finally, the numerical examples and analysis of convergence properties suggest a possible connection to optimization and learning theory (cs.LG).
